ABOUT ME

Almost everything we use and interact with today utilizes some form of computer science. Think about it: What device are you on while reading this story? What framework runs the website this story is on? How is your device connected to the internet that connects you to us?! We're just getting started. Due to computer science, society has undergone a number of changes. Artificial intelligence, for instance. AI helps doctors detect diseases. Using self-driving cars reduces the use of fossil fuels and takes your hands off the wheel. Programs that project the spread of forest fires and the most efficient way to combat them, and so on. Currently, our planet is going through a period of unprecedented change, which is changing the way we live and work. Any job that can be automated will be replaced by new technology. To move ahead, we'll need more skills. These shifts aren't new, and they will continue to become more pronounced. How can you ensure that you have a fair shot at success in this new expanding economy? All in all, code is the language of the 21st century. The most effective way to enter the world of computer programming is through schools or through alternative programs. As a software engineer, I was inspired to create an online camp to help marginalized youth who cannot attend college adjust to these changes. In our digital age, computer science and the demand for computer engineers continue to grow exponentially. And becoming digitally literate is the first step to accessing tomorrow's career opportunities. At Youth Who Code, we are so proud of our students who have begun exploring and developing their computer science skills. Because we know where those skills will take them. To an ever-brighter future!
